The hedgehogs are struggling to keep up with the monthly bills so they hold a yard sale. All is going well... until Sonic's master Bartleby shows up to discipline him.

comments.text:
You probably arent paying much attention then man. Once, after my fifth run through of the series, tried to watch the series out of order and focus on my favorite episodes. It was a huge mistake. The episodes simply dont make sense when you understand some of the subtext and foreshadowing.  In fact, it can be distracting to not watch it in order. Some people think this show is just a joke or a shitpost but its actually really deep and dabbles with serious themes. Especially with long term arcs. Frankly, if you really think you can or should watch this series out of order (or skip a single episode) you arent watching it correctly bro.
I get that it can be difficult to care. Most of these episodes are awesome on their own, mostly because of the writing and animation quality. But its maybe 10 to 100 times better when you actually know the deep lore.
